> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Tomato-Cucumber Salad ==

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Trim and halve @mini cucumber{2}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); slice into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Pick and finely chop fronds from @dill{¼%ounce}(finely chopped).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato and cucumbers; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside, stirring occasionally.

== Israeli Couscous ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

== Garlicky Steak ==

While couscous cooks, pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak; cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Dill Crema ==

While steak cooks, pour liquid from tomato and cucumber salad into a #small bowl{}. Set salad aside.

To bowl with liquid, add @crema{1.5%tablespoon}, half the dill, remaining @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}; stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Assembly ==

Toast @pita bread{2} until softened and warmed through; cut into quarters.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of olive oil and as much remaining dill as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide couscous between shallow #bowls{}. Top with tomato and cucumber salad, steak, and dill crema; serve with pita wedges alongside.